meanings: (재산·목숨·나라 등을) guard; (방어하다) defend, protect; (보호하다) look after, take care of
(약속·법·질서 등을) keep, obey, follow, observe, stick[adhere] to, uphold

examples.korean: He had dishonoured nearly all of his election pledges. 발음듣기 그는 거의 모든 선거 공약을 지키지 않았었다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary

examples.korean: They have signally failed to keep their election promises. 발음듣기 그들은 선거 공약을 분명히 지키지 못했다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary

examples.korean: He failed to keep the appointment. 발음듣기 그는 그 약속을 지키지 않았다[못했다]. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary

examples.korean: It would have been dishonourable of her not to keep her promise. 발음듣기 그녀가 약속을 지키지 않았으면 수치스러웠을 것이다. Oxford Advanced Learner's English-Korean Dictionary
